# UI scale

For **typography** (weight, font slot), see [text-typography.mdc](Mobile/.cursor/rules/text-typography.mdc).

## Source of truth

| What | Location |
|------|----------|
| Types | [`constants/uiScale/types.ts`](Mobile/constants/uiScale/types.ts) |
| Profiles | [`constants/uiScale/profiles/*.ts`](Mobile/constants/uiScale/profiles/) |
| Registry | [`constants/uiScale/index.ts`](Mobile/constants/uiScale/index.ts) → `UI_SCALE_PROFILES` |
| Resolvers | [`utils/resolvers/resolveUiScale.ts`](Mobile/utils/resolvers/resolveUiScale.ts), hooks in [`useResolvedUiScale.ts`](Mobile/utils/resolvers/useResolvedUiScale.ts) |

## Profile organization

```
global
common       → { buttons }     // back, share, save, filter, externalLink
preview      → { text, icon, buttons }
pageScreen   → { text, buttons }
map          → { text, buttons }
filter       → { text, icon, buttons }
betaSection  → { text, buttons }
tabs         → { buttons }       // tabBar (icon + text)
toast        → { text, buttons }
regionScreen → { text }
infoScreen   → { text }
```

**Placement rules:**

- **`text`** — non-button copy (titles, labels, notes, marker labels).
- **`icon`** — standalone icons not tied to a named button component.
- **`buttons`** — one entry per **named button component** in **lowerCamelCase**; each button appears **once** in the profile.
- **`common.buttons`** — buttons reused across screen contexts.
- **Base pixel sizes live in components**; profiles hold multipliers/specs only.

## Scale spec types

| Spec | Properties | Resolves to |
|------|------------|-------------|
| **`ConstantTextSizeSpec`** | `default`, `floor?`, `ceiling?`, `accessibilityScaling?` | Fixed px font size |
| **`ScalingTextSizeSpec`** | `default`, `floor?`, `ceiling?`, `computeFloorFromAccessibilityScaling?`, … | `{ maxFontSize, minFontSize }` |
| **`IconScaleSpec`** | `scale`, `accessibilityScalingStrength?` | Multiplier on base icon px |
| **`ButtonScaleSpec`** | `background?`, `icon?`, `text?`, `selectable?` | Independent bg / icon / text / control scales |

**`ButtonScaleSpec` semantics:**

- `background` — pill/circle/hit-target shell and padding (`IconScaleSpec`; follows accessibility scaling when enabled).
- `icon` — glyph inside the button, or trailing row icons on filter checkbox rows (route-type badges, source logos).
- `text` — label on the button (`ConstantTextSizeSpec` or `ScalingTextSizeSpec`).
- `subtext` — secondary copy paired with the control (hints, chevrons).
- `selectable` — checkbox, radio, switch chrome (`IconScaleSpec`).

**Circular button pattern:**

```typescript
const { size, iconScale } = useResolvedButtonDimensions(
  uiScale.common.buttons.back,
  STANDARD_BUTTON_SIZE,
  designIconScale, // optional component-local ratio
);
```

## Accessibility scaling

1. **`UiScaleGlobal.accessibilityScaling`** — profile-wide (`Auto` on; `Small`/`Medium`/`Large` off).
2. **Per-token override** — `accessibilityScaling?` on any text/icon spec.
3. **Text (constant)** — `defaultStep * clamp(deviceFontScale)` then `floor`/`ceiling`.
4. **Text (scaling)** — max from constant path; min from `floor` or `computedFloorConstant * fontScale`.
5. **Icons** — `scale * (1 + (clampedFontScale - 1) * strength)` when global accessibility is on.
6. **Button background** — resolved via `IconScaleSpec` (same accessibility behavior as icons).
7. Always `allowFontScaling={false}` on token-driven text.

## Extending scale definitions

**New UI scale profile:** copy a profile file, adjust values, register in `UI_SCALE_PROFILES`.

**New token under existing category:** extend type in `types.ts`, add inline values to **all four** profiles, wire via resolver hooks.

**New button token:** lowerCamelCase name matching component; use `common.buttons` only when shared across contexts; populate only the `ButtonScaleSpec` fields the button uses.

## Do's / Don'ts

- Use resolvers / `useResolved*` hooks; multiply **component base px** by resolved scales.
- Decouple button background, icon, text, and selectable — never derive icon size from text fontSize.
- Do not hardcode profile-dependent px in StyleSheets.
- Do not use helper functions inside profile definitions — inline objects only.
